ciscoFcipMgmtMIB.name: ciscoFcipMgmtMIB

revisions.description: Changed the MAX-ACCESS of cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntWWN from read-create to read-write.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoFcipMgmtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553 -NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoFcipMgmtMIB.description: The Fibre Channel Over TCP/IP management MIB module. This mib module is the Cisco version of the FCIP MIB draft , draft-ietf-ips-fcip-mib-02.txt, from the IETF.

CfmFcEntityMode.name: CfmFcEntityMode
CfmFcEntityMode.description: The type of port mode provided by an FCIP Entity for a FCIP Link. An FCIP Entity can be an E-Port mode for one of its FCIP Link Endpoints, an B-Port mode for another of its FCIP Link Endpoints. ePortMode(1) - entity mode is e_port. bPortMode(2) - entity mode is b_port. other(3) - entity mode is some other port.

cfmFcipDynIpConfType.name: cfmFcipDynIpConfType
cfmFcipDynIpConfType.description: The type of discovery protocol used to discover remote FCIP entities. slpv2(1) - Service Location Protocol. none(2) - nothing is used.

cfmFcipFabricWWN.name: cfmFcipFabricWWN
cfmFcipFabricWWN.description: The World Wide Name of this FCIP device. The zero-length string value is used in circumstances where the WWN is unassigned/unknown.

cfmFcipEntityInstanceTable.name: cfmFcipEntityInstanceTable
cfmFcipEntityInstanceTable.description: A table containing FCIP entity specific information.

cfmFcipEntityInstanceEntry.name: cfmFcipEntityInstanceEntry
cfmFcipEntityInstanceEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP entity table containing information about a particular FCIP entity.

cfmFcipEntityAddressType.name: cfmFcipEntityAddressType
cfmFcipEntityAddressType.description: The type of Internet address by which the entity is reachable.

cfmFcipEntityAddress.name: cfmFcipEntityAddress
cfmFcipEntityAddress.description: The Internet address for this entity.

cfmFcipEntityTcpConnPort.name: cfmFcipEntityTcpConnPort
cfmFcipEntityTcpConnPort.description: A TCP port other than the FCIP Well-Known port on which the FCIP entity listens for new TCP connection requests. It contains the value zero (0) if the FCIP Entity only listens on the Well-Known port.

cfmFcipEntitySACKOption.name: cfmFcipEntitySACKOption
cfmFcipEntitySACKOption.description: An indication of whether the TCP Selective Acknowledgement Option is enabled to allow the receiver end to acknowledge multiple lost packets in a singel ACK, enabling faster recovery. enabled(1) - acknowledge option is enabled. disabled(2) - acknowledge option is disabled.

cfmFcipEntitySeqNumWrap.name: cfmFcipEntitySeqNumWrap
cfmFcipEntitySeqNumWrap.description: An indication of whether the FCIP Entity supports the protection against sequence number wrap. If true(1), the FCIP Entity supports protection against sequence number wrap. If false(2), the FCIP Entity does not support protection against sequence number wrap.

cfmFcipEntityPHBSupport.name: cfmFcipEntityPHBSupport
cfmFcipEntityPHBSupport.description: An indication of whether the FCIP Entity supports PHB IP QoS.

cfmFcipEntityStatus.name: cfmFcipEntityStatus
cfmFcipEntityStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cfmFcipLinkTable.name: cfmFcipLinkTable
cfmFcipLinkTable.description: A table containing FCIP link specific information.

cfmFcipLinkEntry.name: cfmFcipLinkEntry
cfmFcipLinkEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP link table containing information about a particular FCIP link.

cfmFcipLinkIndex.name: cfmFcipLinkIndex
cfmFcipLinkIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies one FCIP link within a FCIP entity.

cfmFcipLinkIfIndex.name: cfmFcipLinkIfIndex
cfmFcipLinkIfIndex.description: A unique value that identifies the interface on this FCIP device to which this link pertains. The interface identified by a particular value of this object is the same interface as identified by the same value of the ifIndex object, defined in IF-MIB.

cfmFcipLinkCost.name: cfmFcipLinkCost
cfmFcipLinkCost.description: The cost associated with this FCIP Link. The link cost is used to select lowest cost route.

cfmFcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode.name: cfmFcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode
cfmFcipLinkLocalFcipEntityMode.description: The mode of the local FCIP Entity to which this FCIP Link pertains.

cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN.name: cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN
cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityWWN.description: The World Wide Name of the remote FC Fabric Entity. If this is a zero length string then this link would accept connections from any remote entity. If a WWN is specified then this link would accept connections from a remote entity with this WWN.

cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddrType.name: cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddrType
cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddrType.description: The type of Internet address by which the remote FCIP entity is reachable.

cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress.name: cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress
cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityAddress.description: The Internet address for the remote FCIP entity.

cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityMode.name: cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityMode
cfmFcipLinkRemFcipEntityMode.description: The mode of the remote FCIP Entity to which this FCIP Link pertains.

cfmFcipLinkStatus.name: cfmFcipLinkStatus
cfmFcipLinkStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cfmFcipTcpConnTable.name: cfmFcipTcpConnTable
cfmFcipTcpConnTable.description: A table containing FCIP specific information about this FCIP device's existing TCP connections. The FCIP TCP Connection table contains information about existing TCP connections. Each FCIP link within a FCIP entity manages one or more TCP connections. The FCIP entity employs a Data Engine for each TCP connection for handling FC frame encapsulation, de-encapsulation and transmission of FCIP frames on the connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnEntry.name: cfmFcipTcpConnEntry
cfmFcipTcpConnEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP TCP Connection table containing information about a particular TCP connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnLocalPort.name: cfmFcipTcpConnLocalPort
cfmFcipTcpConnLocalPort.description: The local port number for this TCP connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnRemPort.name: cfmFcipTcpConnRemPort
cfmFcipTcpConnRemPort.description: The remote port number for this TCP connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnPurpose.name: cfmFcipTcpConnPurpose
cfmFcipTcpConnPurpose.description: The nature of messages that get transmitted on this TCP connection. control(1) - TCP connection is for control purpose. data(2) - TCP connection is for data purpose. both(3) - TCP connection is for control and data purpose.

cfmFcipTcpConnRWSize.name: cfmFcipTcpConnRWSize
cfmFcipTcpConnRWSize.description: The default maximum TCP Receiver Window size for this TCP connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnMSS.name: cfmFcipTcpConnMSS
cfmFcipTcpConnMSS.description: The TCP Maximum Segment Size (MSS) for this TCP connection.

cfmFcipTcpConnTimeOut.name: cfmFcipTcpConnTimeOut
cfmFcipTcpConnTimeOut.description: The timeout value for this TCP connection.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteTable.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteTable
cfmFcipDynamicRouteTable.description: A table containing FCIP Route specific information. The FCIP dynamic route table contains information about this FCIP device's routing information that is dynamically discovered. The FCIP device may use SLPv2 protocol in conjunction with other protocols, say FSPF, for dynamically discovering other FCIP entities, and populate this table for Destination Address Identifier to connecting FCIP link information.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteEntry.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteEntry
cfmFcipDynamicRouteEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Dynamic Route Table containing information about a particular FCIP route.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteIndex.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteIndex
cfmFcipDynamicRouteIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the FCIP dynamic Route table.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteDID.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteDID
cfmFcipDynamicRouteDID.description: The 8 bit ID of a Fibre Channel Domain that is reachable from this FCIP device.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex
cfmFcipDynamicRouteLinkIndex.description: The FCIP Link that is represented by this value in the FCIP Link table used to reach this domain (specified by the previous object 'cfmFcipDynamicRouteDID') on the remote FCIP device.

cfmFcipStaticRouteTable.name: cfmFcipStaticRouteTable
cfmFcipStaticRouteTable.description: A table containing FCIP Route specific information. The FCIP static route table contains information about this FCIP device's routing information that is created by the Network Admin. In the absence of dynamic discovery of remote FCIP entities, the Network Manager will figure out all the remote FCIP devices that are reachable from this device, and populate this table with FCIP link information for each Domain Id.

cfmFcipStaticRouteEntry.name: cfmFcipStaticRouteEntry
cfmFcipStaticRouteEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Static Route Table containing information about a particular FCIP route.

cfmFcipStaRtIndex.name: cfmFcipStaRtIndex
cfmFcipStaRtIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the FCIP static Route table.

cfmFcipStaRtDID.name: cfmFcipStaRtDID
cfmFcipStaRtDID.description: The 8 bit ID of a Fibre Channel Domain that is reachable from this FCIP device.

cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntWWN.name: cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntWWN
cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntWWN.description: The World Wide Name of the remote FC Entity to which this route applies.

cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntId.name: cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntId
cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntId.description: The identifier of the remote FCIP entity to which this route pertains.

cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddrType.name: cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddrType
cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddrType.description: The type of Internet address used by the remote FCIP entity to which this route pertains.

cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddr.name: cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddr
cfmFcipStaRtRemFcipEntAddr.description: The Internet address for the remote FCIP entity.

cfmFcipStaRtStatus.name: cfmFcipStaRtStatus
cfmFcipStaRtStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

cfmFcipLinkErrorsTable.name: cfmFcipLinkErrorsTable
cfmFcipLinkErrorsTable.description: A table containing error counters for FCIP Links. The FCIP Link Errors Table contains counters that indicate the number of times each error case happened that caused closing down a TCP connection.

cfmFcipLinkErrorsEntry.name: cfmFcipLinkErrorsEntry
cfmFcipLinkErrorsEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP Link Errors Table containing error counters for a FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs
cfmFcipLinkFcipLossofFcSynchs.description: The number of times FC synchronization lost on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSfNotRcv.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSfNotRcv
cfmFcipLinkFcipSfNotRcv.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame not received on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespNotRcv.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespNotRcv
cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespNotRcv.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame Response not received on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatch.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatch
cfmFcipLinkFcipSfRespMismatch.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame Bytes mismatch happened on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonce.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonce
cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidNonce.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frame Invalid connections once happened on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipDuplicateSfRcv.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipDuplicateSfRcv
cfmFcipLinkFcipDuplicateSfRcv.description: The number of times duplicate FCIP Special Frames received on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWN.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWN
cfmFcipLinkFcipSfInvalidWWN.description: The number of times FCIP Special Frames with invalid destination FC Fabric Entity WWN received on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOut.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOut
cfmFcipLinkFcipBB2LkaTimeOut.description: The number of times B_Access Link Keep Alive Time out happened on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkFcipSntpTimeStampExp.name: cfmFcipLinkFcipSntpTimeStampExp
cfmFcipLinkFcipSntpTimeStampExp.description: The number of times SNTP Time Stamp expired on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors.name: cfmFcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors
cfmFcipLinkTcpTooManyErrors.description: The number of times TCP connections with too many errors closed down on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkTcpKeepAliveTimeOut.name: cfmFcipLinkTcpKeepAliveTimeOut
cfmFcipLinkTcpKeepAliveTimeOut.description: The number of times TCP connections that experienced TCP Keep Alive Time outs closed down on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkTcpExDatagramsDropped.name: cfmFcipLinkTcpExDatagramsDropped
cfmFcipLinkTcpExDatagramsDropped.description: The number of times TCP connections that dropped excessive number of datagrams closed down on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatch.name: cfmFcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatch
cfmFcipLinkTcpSaParamMismatch.description: The number of times TCP connections with SA parameter mismatches closed down on this FCIP Link.

cfmFcipEntityScalarGroup.name: cfmFcipEntityScalarGroup
cfmFcipEntityScalarGroup.description: A collection of scalar objects applicable to all FCIP instances.

cfmFcipEntityInstanceGroup.name: cfmFcipEntityInstanceGroup
cfmFcipEntityInstanceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP instances.

cfmFcipLinkGroup.name: cfmFcipLinkGroup
cfmFcipLinkGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links.

cfmFcipTcpConnGroup.name: cfmFcipTcpConnGroup
cfmFcipTcpConnGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP TCP conections.

cfmFcipDynamicRouteGroup.name: cfmFcipDynamicRouteGroup
cfmFcipDynamicRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP dynamic routes.

cfmFcipStaticRouteGroup.name: cfmFcipStaticRouteGroup
cfmFcipStaticRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP static routes.

cfmFcipLinkErrorsGroup.name: cfmFcipLinkErrorsGroup
cfmFcipLinkErrorsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP link errors.
